method and block level scopes

//block

block is either a  {}  or do/end,  invokes a method in  general, creates a new scope

toatal = 0
[1, 2, 3].each { |number| total += number }
puts total

---

total = 0
[1, 2, 3].each do |number|
  total += number
end
puts total


// sample snippet
10.times do |number|
 number.times { |number| print '*' }
  puts
end

// types of variables

CONSTANT = value  // acccessible in all scopes, cant be initialized in methods

$global_variable   // starts with $ (avoid if possible)

@@class_variable   // when no need of instances having thier own value,
                   // class can access it as well

@instace_variable  //

